{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:sirach.19",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 19,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 19 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.19.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:1",
      "text": "A worker who is a drunkard will not become rich. He who despises small things will fall little by little.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.19.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:2",
      "text": "Wine and women will make men of understanding go astray. He who joins with prostitutes is reckless.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.19.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:3",
      "text": "Decay and worms will have him as their heritage. A reckless soul will be taken away.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.19.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:4",
      "text": "He who is hasty to trust is shallow-hearted. He who sins offends against his own soul.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.19.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:5",
      "text": "He who rejoices in wickedness will be condemned.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.19.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:6",
      "text": "He who hates gossip has less wickedness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.19.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:7",
      "text": "Never repeat what is told you, and you won’t lose anything.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.19.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:8",
      "text": "Whether it is of friend or foe, don’t tell it. Unless it is a sin to you, don’t reveal it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.19.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:9",
      "text": "For if he has heard you and observed you, when the time comes, he will hate you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.19.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:10",
      "text": "Have you heard something? Let it die with you. Be brave: it will not make you burst!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.19.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:11",
      "text": "A fool will travail in pain with a word, as a woman in labor with a child.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.19.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:12",
      "text": "As an arrow that sticks in the flesh of the thigh, so is gossip in a fool.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.19.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:13",
      "text": "Question a friend; it may be he didn’t do it. If he did something, it may be that he may do it no more.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.19.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:14",
      "text": "Question your neighbor; it may be he didn’t say it. If he has said it, it may be that he may not say it again.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.19.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:15",
      "text": "Question a friend; for many times there is slander. Don’t trust every word.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.19.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:16",
      "text": "There is one who slips, and not from the heart. Who is he who hasn’t sinned with his tongue?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.19.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:17",
      "text": "Reprove your neighbor before you threaten him; and give place to the law of the Most High.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.19.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:20",
      "text": "All wisdom is the fear of the Lord. In all wisdom is the doing of the law.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.19.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:22",
      "text": "The knowledge of wickedness is not wisdom. The prudence of sinners is not counsel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.19.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:23",
      "text": "There is a wickedness, and it is an abomination. There is a fool lacking in wisdom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.19.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:24",
      "text": "Better is one who has little understanding, and fears God, than one who has much intelligence and transgresses the law.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.19.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:25",
      "text": "There is an exquisite subtlety, and it is unjust. And there is one who perverts favor to gain a judgment.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.19.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:26",
      "text": "There is one who does wickedly, who hangs down his head with mourning; but inwardly he is full of deceit,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.19.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:27",
      "text": "bowing down his face, and pretending to be deaf in one ear. Where he isn’t known, he will take advantage of you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.19.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:28",
      "text": "And if for lack of power he is hindered from sinning, if he finds opportunity, he will do mischief.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.19.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:29",
      "text": "A man will be known by his appearance. One who has understanding will be known by his face when you meet him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.19.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 19:30",
      "text": "A man’s attire, grinning laughter, and the way he walks show what he is.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
